      "message": "If the compiler can see this, lots of times it\u0027ll just skip it if you\u0027re overwriting all the bytes.  Sometimes it\u0027ll even just zero the bytes you don\u0027t later overwrite.  I stand by this memset as a good idea that delivers more safety than runtime expense.  It\u0027s usually cheaper than it looks. :)  (I mean, most of the time this will be a register xor\u0027d with itself... there\u0027s literally no cheaper instruction.)",
